informationWithheld: Coordinate uncertainty increased to 27158m to protect threatened taxon
verbatimLocality: Oregon, Lewis and Clark National Historic Trail, US
identificationRemarks: At first, going with Dicamptodon species, I was going to suggest it was D. copei because of the relatively small head, long body, and short legs, but then I noticed the fir needles! This salamander is tiny! Okay, then I noticed the lack or near lack of gills, and the tiny white spots along the sides, along with the small head, long body, short legs and toes.... Torrent Salamander; by range this would be Cascade Torrent Salamander. Nice find.
